<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,310,669,695]" box="[189,310,669,695]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,669,695]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,669,695]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[188,1399,717,852]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Flowers with reduced, apically 3-lobed corona lobes. Similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1003,1148,717,742]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hemipogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acerosus">
<emphasis box="[1003,1148,717,742]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">H. acerosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the acicular leaves, sessile cymes and urceolate corolla, internally bearded along the lobe basal half, but can be distinguished by the opposite leaves (vs verticillate in 
<taxonomicName box="[816,953,790,815]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hemipogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acerosus">
<emphasis box="[816,953,790,815]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">H. acerosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and presence of a corona (vs absence in 
<taxonomicName box="[219,358,826,851]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hemipogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acerosus">
<emphasis box="[219,358,826,851]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">H. acerosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,971,892,966]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,324,892,918]" box="[189,324,892,918]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,892,918]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,892,918]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,971,939,966]" box="[189,971,939,966]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
The epithet ʻ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bitencourt &amp; Santos &amp; Snak &amp; Rapini" authorityYear="2020" box="[339,453,939,965]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hemipogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trilobatus">
<emphasis box="[339,453,939,965]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">trilobatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ʼ refers to the apically 3-lobed corona lobes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
