<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,578,264,291]" box="[189,578,264,291]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,578,264,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,578,264,291]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Provisional conservation status</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[188,1400,312,589]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName authority="Bitencourt &amp; Santos &amp; Snak &amp; Rapini, 2020" authorityName="Bitencourt &amp; Santos &amp; Snak &amp; Rapini" authorityYear="2020" box="[189,448,312,338]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hemipogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trilobatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,448,312,338]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Hemipogon trilobatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[457,548,312,338]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is known from only two collections, both near the S„o Bento waterfall, in Chapada dos Veadeiros. Specimen labels provide no information about population density. However, the species is known to occur in a tourist location, surrounded by farms and cattle raising, has an area of occupancy (AOO) estimated at 
<quantity box="[604,664,419,445]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="km" value="8.0">8 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="right" box="[665,674,418,432]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">2</superScript>
, probably under continuing decline in geographic range and habitat quality. During fieldwork in the 
<typeStatus box="[676,727,455,481]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">type</typeStatus>
locality, we did not find any specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bitencourt &amp; Santos &amp; Snak &amp; Rapini, 2020" authorityName="Bitencourt &amp; Santos &amp; Snak &amp; Rapini" authorityYear="2020" box="[1245,1398,455,481]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hemipogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trilobatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1245,1398,455,481]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">H. trilobatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[189,281,491,517]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and the new species has not been recollected since 1994. Based on criteria B2ab(i,ii,iii,iv) of the International Union for Conservation of Nature (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[799,939,526,552]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refId="ref4310" refString="IUCN. 2019. Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria, Version 14. IUCN, Gland / Cambridge." type="book" year="2019">IUCN 2019</bibRefCitation>
) Red List assessment, we provisionally classify the species as Critically Endangered (CR).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,388,628,654]" box="[189,388,628,654]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,388,628,654]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,388,628,654]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Taxonomic note</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,675,844]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName authority="Bitencourt &amp; Santos &amp; Snak &amp; Rapini, 2020" authorityName="Bitencourt &amp; Santos &amp; Snak &amp; Rapini" authorityYear="2020" box="[189,448,675,701]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hemipogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trilobatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,448,675,701]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Hemipogon trilobatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[457,549,676,702]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has narrow leaves, urceolate corolla with bearded lobes and was found in a savannah of Central 
<collectingCountry box="[481,556,711,737]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Together, these features support its classification in 
<taxonomicName box="[1169,1306,712,737]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hemipogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[1169,1306,712,737]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Hemipogon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1313,1374,711,737]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
It most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[470,609,747,772]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hemipogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acerosus">
<emphasis box="[470,609,747,772]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">H. acerosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the acicular leaves and sessile cymes, but differs from all other taxa in the genus by the opposite leaves and flowers with reduced corona lobes, as presented in the key below and 
<tableCitation box="[367,455,818,844]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="6.[189,258,265,291]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Table 1. Diagnostic characters to distinguish the species of Hemipogon s. str." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/3A926641FF9A463174A9FEFFFB92FE12" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" tableUuid="3A926641FF9A463174A9FEFFFB92FE12">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
